competitor /kəmˈpɛtɪtə/

(competitors) 

1. N-COUNT A company's competitors are companies who are trying to sell similar goods or services to the same people. 竞争对手 

例： The bank isn't performing as well as some of its competitors. 这家银行没有它的一些竞争对手表现好。 

2. N-COUNT A competitor is a person who takes part in a competition or contest. 参赛者 

例： One of the oldest competitors won the individual silver medal. 其中一个年纪最大的参赛者赢得了个人银牌。

</div>

